They are kept by the old city of Tel-Aviv, Jaffa, on the shore of the Mediterranean Sea.
It is crossed by the famous Via Maris that connects Egypt, Syria, Anatoly and Mesopotamia.
The city is mentioned in the Greek and Egyptian legends of antiquity.
According to legend, this is where Noah built his ark and that Perseus saved the beautiful Andromede, with whom he lived here himself a long and happy life.
Tourists particularly like to walk in narrow streets that bear the name of the zodiac signs.
