Spijkenisse, a sleeping town that has nothing to do with the doors of Rotterdam, holds a quite particular record.
The municipality of 80,000 souls shows the lowest rate of education in the Netherlands.
In order to restore some neurons to the brains, the city decided a few years ago to contribute to the general culture and reproduce the seven fictional bridges on the euro banknotes in the form of beautiful small miniatures of painted reinforced concrete.
The success of the cultural offensive remained limited.
This is how the city authorities realized that there was only one way to get back to the statistics: the construction of a library!
Winy Maas, from Rotterdam MVRDV's office of architects, master of bold building diagrams and creator of mind-filled buildings and often cynics, accepted the project with its usual phlegm and attended the competition in 2003 with five books under the arm and a lace on the face.
