After harvesting large sulphur rocks, which weigh almost 70 kilos in total, he installs them in two bamboo baskets that he loads on his shoulders through the steep trails.
There is only 250 meters to the top of the volcano that peaks at 2,386 meters high, but exhausted carriers take more than 40 minutes to climb this distance, to a turtle allure, keeping the balance and measuring their steps so as not to trip and fall into the precipice.
They know that a fake could not cost them their lives, as it happened to a French tourist who took a deadly fall in the Kawah Ijen volcano several years ago.
