The confirmation of the two presidents that they would submit to the ICJ took place after Colombia had denounced this week the Bogota Pact by which it had agreed to submit to the decisions of this international tribunal, after a decision on the maritime limits with Nicaragua that it considered to be gravely erroneous.
The summit was held without the presence of the presidents of Brazil, Dilma Rouseff, Venezuela, Hugo Chávez, Bolivia, Evo Morales, and Argentina, Cristina Kirchner.
Paraguay, suspended from Unasur since 2011 after the removal of its former President Fernando Lugo, did not participate in the meeting.
